name: Zucchini Bread
description: A moist, spiced bread is a great way to use up summer zucchini.

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 350° F. Butter and flour an 8 by 4-inch loaf pan. In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, baking soda, baking powder, and salt.
In a large bowl, whisk together egg and sugar. Add vegetable oil and whisk until well combined. Stir in zucchini, then vanilla extract.
Add flour mixture to wet ingredients and stir until well combined. Pour batter into loaf pan. Bake until a cake tester comes out clean, about 50 minutes.
